    <div style="background: #eff6ff; border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6; padding: 1rem 1.2rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
      <strong>🎯 The honest answer:</strong> If you have no specific connection to Taiwan, start with Pinyin. It opens up 95% of Chinese learning resources. You can always add Zhuyin later — and the transition is surprisingly easy since the sounds are identical.
