    <!-- Learning Both -->
    <h2 id="learning-both">Learning Both: The Best Approach</h2>

    <p>Many serious Chinese learners eventually learn both systems. Here is the recommended path:</p>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 1.2rem; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
      <div style="background: #eff6ff; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.2rem; text-align: center;">
        <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: bold; color: #3b82f6;">Phase 1</div>
        <strong>Weeks 1-4</strong>
        <p style="font-size: 0.92rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0;">Learn your primary system thoroughly. Master all initials, finals, and tones. Use our <a href="/chinese/tools/tone-trainer/">Tone Trainer</a> daily.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background: #fef3c7; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.2rem; text-align: center;">
        <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: bold; color: #eab308;">Phase 2</div>
        <strong>Months 2-6</strong>
        <p style="font-size: 0.92rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0;">Build vocabulary and reading skills using your primary system. Focus on characters, not phonetics.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background: #dcfce7; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.2rem; text-align: center;">
        <div style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: bold; color: #22c55e;">Phase 3</div>
        <strong>Month 6+</strong>
        <p style="font-size: 0.92rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0;">Add the second system. Since you already know all the sounds, you only need to learn new symbols. Use our <a href="/chinese/tools/zhuyin-converter/">Zhuyin Converter</a> to practice mapping.</p>
