    </div>

    <!-- Typing -->
    <h2 id="typing-input">Typing and Input Methods</h2>

    <p>Your choice of phonetic system also affects how you type Chinese on devices:</p>

    <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
      <thead>
        <tr style="background: #f1f5f9;">
          <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align: left;">Feature</th>
          <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align: left;">Pinyin Input</th>
          <th style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0; text-align: left;">Zhuyin Input</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Keyboard layout</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Standard QWERTY — same as English</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Special layout (symbols mapped to keys)</td></tr>
        <tr style="background: #f8fafc;"><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Phone setup</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Built-in on all smartphones</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Built-in on all smartphones (add keyboard)</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Typing speed</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Fast if you type English fast</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Can be faster once memorized (fewer keystrokes)</td></tr>
        <tr style="background: #f8fafc;"><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Learning curve</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Zero — same keys as English</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Moderate — must learn new key positions</td></tr>
        <tr><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Tone input</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Usually optional (smart prediction)</td><td style="padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;">Optional but commonly used for precision</td></tr>
